messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes.
Where is your emergency, sir?
Okay, I live at 201 Rushing Way, Building 1042 in Myrtle Beach.
Okay.
And my neighbor just knocked on my door, and her husband is missing.
We went down to where the mailbox is at, and there's blood and his glasses are there.
Okay. Which building are you in? Your phone cut out, sir.
Building 1042.
What's the apartment number?
It's 201 Rushing Way, Building 1042.
Okay, she's over there with you?
Yes, it's her in the background, crying in my car.
All right, talk to me, please.
Okay, the neighbor came over to me, said her husband was missing.
So I went and looked for him and didn't see him. He never does this. He's not that kind of guy.
She noticed that the keys to the mailbox were missing. We went over there and saw blood on the ground and his glasses.
We didn't touch anything. But we noticed it looks like a trail.
Okay, blood on the ground and the glasses are there?
Yes, and the trail leads towards the bushes but we didn't go look in there.
Okay, please stay on the phone with me.
All right.
So there's a trail of blood leading back to the woods?
Yes, right. We didn't touch anything. I made her get back in the car and drove her back here.
Okay, I'm sending somebody.
All right. Can you give me directions on how to get here?
Sure, go ahead.
River Oaks Drive into Berkshire Forest. Turn left on Augusta Plantation.
Okay, and then keep going straight?
Yes, take another left at Mary Lee Bone and come around past the swimming pool, and it's a townhouse at 201 Rushing Way.
Got it. Were there mailboxes or anything like that on the way?
No, I didn't see anything else.
All right, what's the missing person's name?
Fred Ingalls. F-R-E-D I-N-G-L-E-S.
What's he look like?
He's about six-foot, six-foot-three, tall. Last seen a little while ago.
It's 12:45 in the morning. What time did she last see him?
Around 10 PM. They had pizza together inside the house.
You still there, right?
Yes.
Does she need an ambulance?
Yes, please.
All right, I'll get that arranged. Can you give me your last name?
Rickerson. R-I-C-K-E-R-S-O-N.
First name?
Thomas. First name Thomas.
Thank you, Thomas. Do you know of any reason why he would be missing? Is he involved in anything?
No, no. We're not that kind of people.
All right.
Okay, she's really upset.
We're not going down there without the police. Police are on their way.
Have you tried calling out for him or anything?
Yes, we've done that.
Does he have his wallet or anything? Is that missing, or does he have it with him?
No, he has all that. He just went to check the mail.
And there's blood and glasses on the ground?
That's correct.
The police are coming in now. Talk with them, all right?
All right, thanks.
